From: John Watts <contact@jookia.org>
Date: Tue, 12 Nov 2024 21:34:00 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: test-component: Support continuous rates for test component
Git-commit: c853e96308c58f9a06fcf393bcfe0eabdb72ca9c
Patch-mainline: v6.13-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

There's no reason to limit the supported rates of the test component
to specific ones as if it's a real piece of hardware. Set the rates to
continuous to aid in testing different rates.

Signed-off-by: John Watts <contact@jookia.org>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20241112-alsa_test_rates-v1-1-95cf529db871@jookia.org
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/soc/generic/test-component.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/generic/test-component.c b/sound/soc/generic/test-component.c
index 407288055741..c17abbeafcab 100644
--- a/sound/soc/generic/test-component.c
+++ b/sound/soc/generic/test-component.c
@@ -224,7 +224,7 @@ static const struct snd_soc_dai_ops test_verbose_ops = {
 	.num_auto_selectable_formats	= 1,
 };
 
-#define STUB_RATES	SNDRV_PCM_RATE_8000_384000
+#define STUB_RATES	SNDRV_PCM_RATE_CONTINUOUS
 #define STUB_FORMATS	(SNDRV_PCM_FMTBIT_S8		| \
 			 SNDRV_PCM_FMTBIT_U8		| \
 			 SNDRV_PCM_FMTBIT_S16_LE	| \
